column4: Today (2024-Apr-24) is Mounukhiṓn 16, ἕκτῃ ἐπὶ δέκα Μουνυχιῶνος, day 282 of 354 in the year 2023/2024.

🏺 On this day the Mounikhia (Μουνίχια) was celebrated in Piraeus in in honor of Artemis and after Salamis included commemoration of the goddess’s help in the victory\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Munichia_(festival)

Today (2024-May-09) is Thargēliṓn 1, νουμηνίᾳ Θαργηλιῶνος, day 297 of 354 in the year 2023/2024.
This Thargēliṓn will have 29 days, which the ancient Greeks called a “hollow month” (κοῖλος μήν) as opposed to a “full month” (πλήρης μήν) of 30.
